WEEK 03

Learning Activities & Resources

Switching to WordPress: Moved the SkillSwap AI project from Joomla over to a self-hosted WordPress.org site using CloudAccess.net.
Adding an AI Bot: Used the AI Engine plugin to add a chat bubble to the home page, showing how the "Smart Pairing" feature would look to a user.
Login System: Installed the Ultimate Member plugin to set up the login and sign-up pages for the site.
Design Tweaks: Used the Neve theme to get a clean, pink, and white background and set up the main navigation links.

Estimated Hours
5 hours

Content Insights

This week, I learned that WordPress is quite different from Joomla in how it handles content. 
I used Pages for the main parts of my site, like the home page and the "Problem" section, because they are meant to stay in one place rather than being blog posts.
I also realized that having a clear menu is very important. Even though I have a lot of new pages now (like Login and Account),
I made sure they are all easy to find in the top bar, so anyone visiting the site knows exactly how to use it.

Career/Employability/Learning Insights
Moving my content from Joomla to WordPress taught me that the most important part of a project is the actual idea and text, not just the software you use to build it.
Being able to move my "SkillSwap AI" vision between two different platforms shows that I can adapt to new tools quickly.
I also spent time figuring out the Neve theme settings to make the site look more like a real startup and less like a basic blog.
Getting the colors and layout right is a good skill to have because it makes the work look professional and trustworthy to a potential client or boss.

